        <name xml:lang="en">sodium formate</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Sodium formate is used, e.g., in the pharmaceutical, textile, and leather industries for the buffering and regulating of pH. It also used as a solid deicer in airfields, an enzyme stabilizer in liquid detergents, and as a food preservative (E 237). It is used as an additive in chrome electroplating, in the paper industry, and for stabilization of PVC. Sodium formate can also be used in the production of sodium dithionite.

References:
Daintith, J. (2005) The Facts On File - Dictionary of Chemistry. Market House Books Ltd, USA.
Hietala, J., Vuori, A., Johnsson, P., Pollari, I., Reutemann, W. and Kieczka, H. 2016. Formic Acid. Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry. 1–22.</comment>
